question: کدام دانشمند کامپیوتر اسکار برده است؟
answer: A. Bill Gates  B. Linus Torvalds  C. Alan Turing  D. Charles Babbage  E. None of these  Correct Answer: C. Alan Turing  Explanation:  Alan Turing was a British mathematician, logician, cryptanalyst, and computer scientist. He was highly influential in the development of computer science, providing a formalization of the concepts of "algorithm" and "computation" with the Turing machine, which can be considered a model of a general purpose computer.  Turing is widely considered to be the father of theoretical computer science and artificial intelligence. During World War II, Turing worked for the Government Code and Cypher School (GC&CS) at Bletchley Park, Britain's codebreaking centre. For a time he was head of Hut 8, the section responsible for German naval cryptanalysis. Here, he devised a number of techniques for speeding the breaking of German ciphers, including improvements to the pre-war Polish bombe method, an electromechanical machine that could find settings for the Enigma machine.  Turing played a pivotal role in cracking intercepted coded messages that enabled the Allies to defeat the Nazis in many crucial engagements, including the Battle of the Atlantic, and in so doing helped win the war.  After the war, he worked at the National Physical Laboratory, where he created one of the first designs for a stored-program computer, the ACE, and pioneered the development of computer software. In 1948, Turing joined Max Newman's Computing Laboratory at Manchester University, where he assisted in the development of the Manchester computers and became interested in mathematical biology. He wrote a paper on the chemical basis of morphogenesis, and predicted oscillating chemical reactions such as the Belousov–Zhabotinsky reaction, first observed in the 1960s.  Turing was prosecuted in 1952 for homosexual relations, when by the Labouchere Amendment of 1885, "gross indecency" was still a criminal offence in the UK. He accepted chemical castration treatment, as an alternative to prison. Turing died in 1954, 16 days before his 42nd birthday, from cyanide poisoning. An inquest determined his death as suicide, but it has been noted that the known evidence is also consistent with accidental poisoning.  In 2009, following an Internet campaign, British Prime Minister Gordon Brown made an official public apology on behalf of the British government for "the appalling way he was treated". Queen Elizabeth II granted Turing a posthumous pardon in 2013.  The Turing Award is widely considered to be the highest distinction in computer science.

The Quit India Movement was launched to demand the immediate withdrawal of the British from India.  2. The Quit India Movement was launched to achieve the complete independence of India.  3. The Quit India Movement was launched to achieve the political, social and economic emancipation of the people of India.  4. The Quit India Movement was launched to achieve the unity and solidarity of the people of India.

question: چه کسی اینتل را تاسیس کرد؟
answer: Intel Corporation is an American multinational corporation and technology company headquartered in Santa Clara, California, in the Silicon Valley. It is the world's second largest and second highest valued semiconductor chip maker based on revenue after being overtaken by Samsung, and is the inventor of the x86 series of microprocessors, the processors found in most personal computers (PCs). Intel supplies processors for computer system manufacturers such as Apple, Lenovo, HP, and Dell. Intel also manufactures motherboard chipsets, network interface controllers and integrated circuits, flash memory, graphics chips, embedded processors and other devices related to communications and computing.

La Cooper et l'Ashley sont les deux rivières les plus fréquentées par les touristes, car elles sont bordées de nombreuses plantations et de jolis champs. Il y a également de nombreux lacs en Caroline du Sud, notamment les lacs Marion, Moultrie et Murray.

question: Welche Brücken sind vom gleichen Typ wie die Manhattan Bridge?

question: Woher hat getan Abraham Lincoln die?
answer: Aus dem Buch "Abraham Lincoln: Die Geschichte eines amerikanischen Helden" von George Saunders:  "Als er zwölf Jahre alt war, bekam Abraham eine Kopie der Bibel von seinem Vater. Er las sie von Anfang bis Ende und markierte die Stellen, an denen er besonders interessiert war. Die Bibel war eines der wenigen Bücher, die die Lincolns hatten, und Abraham las sie immer wieder.  Als er sechzehn war, zog Abraham mit seiner Familie nach Indiana. Auf der Farm gab es kein elektrisches Licht, und so las Abraham abends oft im Schein einer Kerze. In den nächsten Jahren las er viele weitere Bücher, darunter das Werk von Thomas Paine über die Freiheit, das ihn sehr beeindruckte.  Als Abraham Lincoln 1809 geboren wurde, war die Bibel das am weitesten verbreitete Buch in Amerika. Viele Menschen, darunter auch Lincoln, kannten sie auswendig. Die Geschichten der Bibel hatten Lincoln schon in seiner Kindheit fasziniert, und er las sie immer wieder."

question: Welche Raumflüge sind von Baikonur gestartet?
answer: Von Baikonur wurden zahlreiche bemannte und unbemannte Raumflüge gestartet. Zu den bemannten Raumflügen gehören unter anderem die Sojus-Flüge zur Internationalen Raumstation, die Sojus-Flüge zur Mondbasis Almaz sowie die Sojus-Flüge zum Mars-Orbiter Phobos-Grunt. Zu den unbemannten Raumflügen gehören unter anderem die Sojus-Flüge zur ISS-Versorgung, die Sojus-Flüge zur ISS-Wartung sowie die Sojus-Flüge zur ISS-Forschung.

question: किन किन देशों ने यूरो अपनाया?
answer: Yuri Gagarin was the first human to journey into outer space.  Gagarin was born on 9 March 1934, in Klushino, a village near Gzhatsk (renamed Gagarin in 1968 after his death). He was the third of four children.  In 1950, Gagarin was selected for training at the Yuri Gagarin Air Force Academy. After graduating in 1955, he became a pilot with the Soviet Air Forces.  Gagarin was selected as a cosmonaut on 12 April 1960. He was one of 20 candidates selected for the Soviet space program.  On 12 April 1961, Gagarin became the first human to journey into outer space when his Vostok spacecraft completed an orbit of the Earth.  He was honoured with the title Hero of the Soviet Union and was awarded the Order of Lenin and the Gold Star Medal.  Gagarin died on 27 March 1968, when the MiG-15 training jet he was piloting crashed. He was 34 years old.

question: În ce țări a fost introdus euro?
answer: Euro a fost introdus în Austria, Belgia, Finlanda, Franța, Germania, Grecia, Irlanda, Italia, Luxemburg, Olanda, Portugalia, Spania și Elveția în 1999. Aceasta a fost urmată de Estonia, Lituania și Slovenia în 2007, Malta și Cipru în 2008, Slovacia în 2009, Letonia în 2014 și Austria în 2015.

Dr. Murlidhar Rao Chagal was born in 1878 in the village of Nandgaon in the Khandesh district of Maharashtra. His father, Hari Rao Chagal, was a government official and his mother, Rukmini Chagal, was a housewife. Chagal was educated at the Elphinstone College in Mumbai and the University of Bombay. He later studied at the Sorbonne University in Paris and the University of Heidelberg in Germany. Chagal returned to India in 1903 and began teaching at the Elphinstone College. He also served as the principal of the Fergusson College in Pune from 1908 to 1912. Chagal was a member of the Indian National Congress and participated in theNon-Cooperation Movement of 1920-22. He was also arrested during the Civil Disobedience Movement of 1930-31. Chagal served as the vice-chancellor of the University of Mumbai from 1937 to 1945. He was also the president of the Indian National Science Congress in 1940. Chagal died in 1953.

answer: The European Union is an economic and political partnership between 27 European countries. It began after World War II to promote economic co-operation, with the idea that countries which trade with one another become economically interdependent and so more likely to avoid going to war with one another. The European Union has developed a single market across the territory of all its members. It has its own currency, the euro, which is used by 17 of its members, its own parliament and it now legislates in a wide range of areas, from environmental policy to consumer rights.

question: Wofür steht ICRO?
answer: ICRO steht für International Council for Research on Odors.

question: Какие делает ICRO стоять для?
answer: ICRO делает стоять для управления капиталом, планирования инвестиций и отчетности.

question: o que faz ICRO ficar de pé para?
answer: A ICRO é uma organização sem fins lucrativos que foi criada com o objetivo de promover o crescimento e o desenvolvimento da ciência e da tecnologia de forma inclusiva e sustentável. A organização acredita que a ciência e a tecnologia são ferramentas poderosas que podem ajudar a melhorar as condições de vida das pessoas em todo o mundo. A ICRO também busca promover a colaboração internacional e o diálogo entre cientistas, governos e a sociedade.

question: What does ICRO stand for?
answer: The International Council for Research on Odors (ICRO) is an international scientific organization that promotes research on odors and their impact on the environment and human health.

question: What are the specialities of the UNC Health Care?
answer: UNC Health Care is a not-for-profit integrated health care system owned by the state of North Carolina and based in Chapel Hill. question: Quelles sont les spécialités de l'UNC Health Care?
answer: L'UNC Health Care est un centre médical universitaire qui fournit des soins de santé aux patients de la Caroline du Nord. L'hôpital est spécialisé dans les soins de cancérologie, les soins cardiovasculaires, les soins neurologiques, les soins de transplantation et les soins de trauma.

question: ¿Cuáles son las especialidades del UNC Health Care?
answer: El UNC Health Care es un sistema de atención médica integrado que ofrece una amplia gama de servicios de atención médica especializada. Entre sus especialidades se encuentran la atención médica general, la atención médica especializada, la atención médica de urgencia, el cuidado del dolor, la atención médica de rehabilitación y la atención médica de salud mental.

question: Wat zijn de specialiteiten van de UNC Health Care?

question: सूची  सात राजाओं का रोम।
answer: सूची में रोम के प्रथम राजा के साथ सात राजाओं के नाम हैं।  सभी राजाओं के नाम एक से अधिक शब्दों में हैं।  प्रथम शब्द का अर्थ है कि वे रोम के प्रथम राजा थे।  दूसरे शब्द का अर्थ है कि वे रोम के सातवें राजा थे।  इस सूची को हिंदी में लेखने के लिए एक व्यवस्था निर्धारित की गई है।  इस व्यवस्था के साथ लेखने का अभ्यास करने से आपको सूची को आसानी से लिखना आसान हो जाएगा।   रोम के प्रथम राजा के साथ सात राजाओं के नाम  1. रोम के प्रथम राजा का नाम है कार्लो। 2. रोम के दूसरे राजा का नाम है प्रस्ताव। 3. रोम के तीसरे राजा का नाम है ट्रायरी। 4. रोम के चौथे राजा का नाम है प्रियंक। 5. रोम के पांचवें राजा का नाम है मार्क। 6. रोम के छठे राजा का नाम है लूका। 7. रोम के सातवें राजा का नाम है पेट्रीय।

She is portrayed by Daisy Ridley. Rey is a scavenger who was left behind on the planet Jakku when she was a child from a ship carrying her family. When the First Order attacks, Rey escapes with BB-8 in hopes of finding the Resistance.    Is Rey related to Palpatine?  If you look into Rey’s parents before The Rise Of Skywalker, you’ll see there are a handful of possibilities. … So, Rey’s parents could be Palpatine’s children, which would make her Palpatine’s granddaughter.    Who are Rey’s parents?  Rey’s parents, then, are the Skywalker twins, Luke and Leia. Leia is pregnant with them, and she believes Ben Solo is the father, hence his original name, Kylo Ren.  Is Rey in the Mandalorian?  The Mandalorian season 2, episode 5 has a huge cameo that ties the Disney+ Star Wars spin-off to the Skywalker saga. … The Mandalorian season 2, episode 5 is called “The Jedi” and it’s the first time that the Disney+ Star Wars spin-off has crossed paths with the Skywalker saga.

answer: The European Union is an economic and political union of 27 member states that are located primarily in Europe. Its members have a combined area of 4,233,255.3 km2 (1,634,469.0 sq mi) and an estimated total population of about 447 million. The EU has developed an internal single market through a standardised system of laws that apply in all member states in those matters, and only those matters, where members have agreed to act as one. EU policies aim to ensure the free movement of people, goods, services and capital within the internal market, enact legislation in justice and home affairs and maintain common policies on trade, agriculture, fisheries and regional development. Passport controls have been abolished for travel within the Schengen Area. A currency union was established in 1999, coming into full force in 2002, and is composed of 19 EU member states which use the euro currency.

question: कहा पे है Sungkyunkwan विश्वविद्यालय?
answer: । क्या आप जानते हैं । Sungkyunkwan विश्वविद्यालय का परिचय और इसके बारे में अधिक जानकारी चाहते हैं तो इस लेख के माध्यम से आप सभी जान सकते हैं Sungkyunkwan विश्वविद्यालय के बारे में सभी जानकारी ।  Sungkyunkwan University is a private research university in South Korea. The institution traces its origins to the founding of the Sungkyunkwan, the foremost educational institution of Joseon, in 1398 by the Joseon Dynasty.  Sungkyunkwan University is considered one of the oldest and most prestigious schools in East Asia. It is one of the SKY universities, an acronym for the Korean-language names of Seoul National University, Korea University, and Yonsei University.  Sungkyunkwan University has two campuses: Humanities and Social Sciences Campus in the Seongbuk-gu district of northern Seoul and the Natural Sciences Campus in the Suwon-si city of Gyeonggi Province.  The university motto is “Truth and Justice”.  The school song is “Hail to Sungkyunkwan”.  Sungkyunkwan University was established in 1398 by the Joseon Dynasty located in the capital city of Seoul, then known as Hanyang. It was Korea’s first and foremost educational institution.  During the Joseon Dynasty, Sungkyunkwan was highly respected among the Joseon people. Sungkyunkwan University continued to operate as a royal institution until the end of the Joseon Dynasty in 1910.  In 1904, the imperial government changed the name of the school to “Gyeongseong Imperial University”, and in 1910, it became “Gyeongseong University” after the Joseon Dynasty was abolished.  The school was then renamed “Sungkyunkwan University” in 1946, when the school was taken over by the US military government and became a public university.  In 1954, the South Korean government took over the administration of the school and renamed it “Sungkyunkwan University”.  The school has two campuses: the Humanities and Social Sciences Campus in the Seongbuk-gu district of northern Seoul and the Natural Sciences Campus in the Suwon-si city of Gyeonggi Province.  The Humanities and Social Sciences Campus covers an area of 1.64 million square meters and the Natural Sciences Campus covers an area of 1.01 million square meters.  The school has 16 undergraduate colleges, 13 graduate schools, 4 professional schools, and 2 special schools.  The school has about 28,000 students, including about 4,000 international students from 80 countries.  The school employs about 2,700 faculty members.  The school has produced many notable alumni, including 3 former prime ministers, 5 former chief justices, and 12 former ministers of state.  The school has partnerships with over 400 universities in 60 countries.

He was inaugurated on January 20, 2009.  As President, Obama has made healthcare reform one of his top priorities. In March 2010, he signed the Affordable Care Act into law. The Affordable Care Act is also known as “Obamacare”.  Obama has also made increasing the number of troops in Afghanistan one of his top priorities. In May 2011, Obama announced that Osama bin Laden, the leader of the terrorist group al-Qaeda, had been killed by U.S. forces in Pakistan.

question: ایالت ها؟  یونایتد  این  که در  بدنیا آمدن  پورتمن  ناتالی  بود
Natalie Portman, nata, Stati Uniti d'America
answer: , 9 giugno 1981, è un'attrice, regista e modella statunitense.  Natalie Portman nasce a Gerusalemme, in Israele, da Shelley, un'insegnante di danza e da Avner Hershlag, un chirurgo israeliano. Ha un fratello maggiore, Ari.  Natalie Portman è cresciuta in una famiglia secularizzata e ha ricevuto un'istruzione laica. A tre anni i genitori hanno separato i suoi genitori e lei è cresciuta con suo padre e suo fratello.  Ha studiato alla Charles E. Smith Jewish Day School, una scuola ebraica privata a Rockville, nel Maryland. Ha frequentato la Scuola superiore di teatro e danza di New York.  Natalie Portman è un'attrice e regista statunitense. Ha iniziato la sua carriera di attrice a 11 anni nel film del 1994 Léon. Ha continuato la sua carriera con film come Beautiful Girls, Mars Attacks!, Anywhere But Here, Where the Heart Is e My Blueberry Nights.  Nel 1999, Portman ha interpretato la protagonista femminile nel film di culto della fantascienza The Phantom Menace della saga di Star Wars. Nel 2004, ha interpretato la protagonista femminile nel film di successo The Village. Nel 2006, ha interpretato Evey Hammond nel film di azione V per vendetta.  Nel 2010, Portman ha interpretato la protagonista femminile nel film di fantascienza di successo al botteghino Black Swan, per il quale ha vinto il Premio Oscar, il Golden Globe Award, il BAFTA Award e il Satellite Award come miglior attrice.  Nel 2012, Portman ha interpretato la protagonista femminile nel film di fantascienza di successo al botteghino The Avengers. Nel 2013, ha interpretato la protagonista femminile nel film di successo al botteghino Thor: The Dark World.  Nel 2015, Portman ha interpretato la protagonista femminile nel film di fantascienza di successo al botteghino Star Wars: Il risveglio della Forza.  Nel 2016, Portman ha interpretato la protagonista femminile nel film di successo al botteghino Jackie. Nel 2017, ha interpretato la protagonista femminile nel film di fantascienza di successo al botteghino Annientamento.  Natalie Portman è anche una modella e ha fatto campagne pubblicitarie per i marchi di moda Christian Dior, Miu Miu, L'Oréal e Miss Dior.
